entry: Don't mean to add this evernt
Key given to operator for checking the beam spot

comment: (1) Beam spot may not be stable so operators will monitor it. We will do blank more often to make sure the beam spot is not drifting.
(1) It's not clear what the problem is. We rebooted CAMAC and reloaded CFDs and GDGs. Still no improvement. Kuan called.

(2) Almost all "resistor" boxes were replaced. Many fast amp channels died so we replaced two modules and used free slots. All the detectors were brought back to life but the gain changed on almost all of them so we had to calibrate them again to roughly 17MeV range.

entry: Took out uB+NW trigger and restart VW HV power crate
Several veto wall PMTs are giving very strange signals which are showing up as very small signals in the QDCS.
Om found that the signal from one VW end went off. More detectors went off in the next few hours.
DAY LIGHT SAVING TIME IN RUN 4098
Operator wants to look at the beam. Key was taken.
Beam lost. Key given to operators.

comment: (1) Previous data had a glom window of 500 clock ticks (1 milisecond). Therefore, many events were being combined together in one buffer.
(1) TDC 127 has a copy at TDC126 for B05 bottom. Before TDC 127 was missing, check the run number. Bar 05 bottom is QDC 08/05 instead of QDC 07/09

(1) The beam was hitting FP slits that were very narrow (5mm). We were getting almost 2k triggers with blank!. Tom opened the slits and the problem got fixed. The rate with blank target dropped to about 10/sec.

entry: End of the first part of the campaign. Gave the key to operator at 11pm.

comment: (1) B21 top HV: (top) changed from 924V to 1024V, (bottom) changed from 952V to 1052V. Somehow, Detector 5 (B04) QDC signal looks good. It's possible one of the cables doesn't have a good contact (OR fast amp connectors).
